name: GGTI-2133 free base
description: An N-acyl-L-amino acid obtained by condensation of the carboxy group of 4-{[(imidazol-4-yl)methyl]amino}-2-(naphthalen-1-yl)benzoic acid with the amino group of L-leucine. An inhibitor of geranylgeranyltransferase type I.

name: S-polyprenyl-L-cysteine zwitterion
description: An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of S-polyprenyl-L-cysteine; major species at pH 7.3.

name: L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion
description: Zwitterionic form of an L-alpha-amino acid having an anionic carboxy group and a protonated amino group.

name: GS-443902
description: An organic triphosphate that is GS-441524 in which the 5'-hydroxy group has been replaced by a triphosphate group. It is the active metabolite of remdesivir.

name: organic triphosphate
description: An organic phosphate ester formed by condensation of triphosphoric acid with one or more alcohols.
